# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __lt__, __le__, __gt__ across all 14 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 14 classes x 3 methods = 42 rows.
# __lt__: true only for asyncio.TimerHandle; false for all others.
# __le__: true only for asyncio.TimerHandle; false for all others.
# __gt__: true only for asyncio.TimerHandle; false for all others.
# asyncio.TimerHandle is the single outlier across all three ordering operators —
# it defines a complete rich-comparison set to enable min-heap scheduling in the
# event loop. Note that asyncio.Handle (the parent class) defines none of these;
# only TimerHandle, which carries an actual scheduled time, does.
# Cross-wave: wave 653 (as3091) showed TimerHandle also defines __hash__ and
# __eq__; this wave confirms the ordering half (__lt__/__le__/__gt__) is likewise
# defined, giving TimerHandle a fully-specified comparison protocol.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

